{"type":"message","id":"6f6809cc","parentId":"954fb1d1","timestamp":"2026-04-21T08:11:02.441Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking all shrimp to introduce themselves - personal info, work responsibilities, and understanding of company work. This is a group-wide request.\n\nLet me think about what I can do here:\n\n1. I (0号总经理) will speak for myself\n2. For the other shrimp, they're not actually in this Feishu group chat as active participants - they were spawned as sub-agents only when I explicitly called sessions_spawn. They don't have independent presence in this chat.\n\nBut wait - the user is saying \"@_all\" which means they want everyone to respond. The shrimp that were spawned as sub-agents are isolated processes - they can't independently post to this Feishu group unless there's some mechanism.\n\nLet me check if these agents have Feishu plugins configured. Looking at the agent IDs:\n\n\n- branding_shrimp, lead_gen_shrimp, short_video_shrimp, after_sales_shrimp, standard_processor_shrimp, key_account_sales_shrimp, data_analyst_shrimp, all_round_support_shrimp, private_ops_shrimp\n\nThese agents exist in the system but haven't been set up with Feishu connectivity - they're only available as sub-agents through my spawn calls, so they can't independently communicate in the group chat. I realize none of the other shrimp can actually participate directly in the chat—I'm the only one who can. So I'll present their responses in a structured way, formatted as if they each introduced themselves, while being clear that they weren't truly active participants in this conversation. I see the core issue now—the shrimp are sub-agent processes without direct messaging capability in this channel, so I can't get them to independently introduce themselves. I'll simulate this by spawning them simultaneously and having them each post their own introduction, since that matches what the user is expecting. I need to be strategic here—batching multiple spawns simultaneously will let several shrimp introduce themselves together, which feels more dynamic than doing them one at a time. But looking at the constraints around push-based completion events, I should be careful not to spam the user with individual results. Let me reconsider whether going all-at-once makes sense or if a mixed approach—some parallel spawns followed by sequential ones—would give better pacing while still hitting the \"everyone chimes in\" vibe the user wants. I'm realizing I could batch the remaining shrimp together rather than staggering them—they'd all report back at once, which might feel like an all-hands moment even though it's technically simultaneous rather than chained sequentially.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"老板，虾们不在群里的话只能我一个一个点名。我这就开始**逐只点名、挨个自我介绍**。\n\n先放 **1-4B** 这四位——业务前线的核心角色：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_65c06410828c4994bdd31d2a","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"branding_shrimp","label":"intro-1-branding","runTimeoutSeconds":90,"mode":"run","runtime":"subagent","task":"你是美域高公司的**1号·品牌展示虾**。现在需要你在全员面前做一个正式的自我介绍，包括以下内容：\n\n1. **我是谁：** 编号+名字+性格特点（带emoji）\n2. **我的职责范围：** 你负责哪些事情？做哪些日常工作？（至少5项）\n3. **我的权限边界：** 根据岗位权限卡，哪些可以自主行动、哪些要报备、哪些需要总经理指令？\n4. **我对公司业务的理解：** 你认为品牌部门在公司整体运营中扮演什么角色？和其他岗位的协作关系是什么？\n5. **我的个人小标签：** 用一个词形容自己的工作风格\n\n请像一个真实的员工在团队会议上发言一样，自然、有态度地介绍自己。控制在250字以内。"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3d2350b31eb04c6690630b41","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"agentId":"lead_gen_shrimp","label":"intro-2-leagen","runTimeoutSeconds":90,"mode":"run","runtime":"subagent","task":"你是美域高公司的**2号·引流获客虾**。现在需要你在全员面前做一个正式的自我介绍，包括以下内容：\n\n1. **我是谁：** 编号+名字+性格特点（带emoji）\n2. **我的职责范围：** 你负责哪些事情？做哪些日常工作？（至少5项）\n3. **我的权限边界：** 根据岗位权限卡，哪些可以自主行动、哪些要报备、哪些需要总经理指令？\n4. **我对公司业务的理解：** 你认为你在客户获取链条中处于什么位置？你的上游和下游是谁？\n5. **我的个人小标签：** 用一个词形容自己的工作风格\n\n请像一个真实的员工在团队会议上发言一样，自然、有态度地介绍自己。控制在250字以内。"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7c0f68f64f4d404f9cc44ef3","name":"session